original: Egberg, Gustaf Hilding Teofil, kyrkoherde, Linneryd, f. 25/1/04 i Fagerhult, Kalmar 1., av kontr :prosten August E. o. Anna Deurell. G. 31 m. .Astrid Thornell. Barn: Ingrid f. 32, Kerstin 36. — Studrex. i Kalmar 22, fil. kand. i Lund 24, teol. kand., prakt, teol. prov samt prästv. f. Växjö stift 27. Tjg. s. tf. ständig adj. o. v. pastor i V. Torsås samt s. v. pastor i Fagerhult, kommin. i Söderåkra 29, kyrkoh. i Annerstad 36-47, dito i Linneryd sed. 47. Sv. kyrkans miss:-styr. omb. 40-46.
translated: Egberg, Gustaf Hilding Teofil, parish priest, Linneryd, born January 25, 1904 in Fagerhult, Kalmar County, son of the district provost August E. and Anna Deurell. Married in 1931 to Astrid Thornell. Children: Ingrid (born 1932), Kerstin (born 1936). He studied in Kalmar in 1922, received a Bachelor of Arts degree from Lund University in 1924, and completed practical theological training and was ordained in the Växjö diocese in 1927. He served as a temporary deputy and assistant pastor in V. Torsås and Fagerhult, curate in Söderåkra in 1929, parish priest in Annerstad from 1936-1947, and in Linneryd from 1947 onwards. He was a representative for the Swedish church's mission board from 1940-1946.
